### AudioToTranscript – VS 2022 HTTP Client Tests
###
### BEFORE RUNNING:
###   1. Run once:  .\TestData\New-TestWav.ps1   (creates TestData/test.wav)
###   2. Terminal 1: azurite --location C:/azurite --loose
###   3. Terminal 2: func start
###   4. Click "Send Request" (▶) above any ### block below — do NOT press F5

@baseUrl  = http://localhost:7071
@boundary = ----AudioTestBoundary7071

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. POST /api/audio — real WAV file attached
#    Expected: 202 Accepted  {"id":"...","status":"queued"}
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### Audio – D|FR Fill Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/audio
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary={{boundary}}

--{{boundary}}
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="metadata"
Content-Type: application/json

{"callType":"D|FR","caseId":"TEST-001","phone":"9794920458","timestamp":"1745000000000","brandId":"4600"}
--{{boundary}}
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="audio"; filename="test.wav"
Content-Type: audio/wav

< ../TestData/test.wav
--{{boundary}}--


